    descriptionEn:
      "At the 52nd Winter National School, Madrasa, and Technical Education Sports Competition, students of Quantum Cosmo School participated in seven events and became champions in five. The events won were: Boys' Table Tennis (Singles), Boys' Table Tennis (Doubles), Girls' Table Tennis (Singles), Boys' Volleyball, and Girls' Basketball. The remaining two events, Girls' Table Tennis (Doubles) and Girls' Volleyball, secured the runner-up position.\n\nThe competition began at the Upazila level on January 11. It progressed through District, Sub-District, and Regional levels, culminating in the final round held in Rajshahi. The closing ceremony and award distribution of the 52nd Winter National Sports Competition-2024 took place on February 12 at Rajshahi Physical Education College Field. The chief guest was Divisional Commissioner Dr. Dewan Muhammad Humayun Kabir, and the event was chaired by Rajshahi Education Board Chairman Professor Dr. Oliul Alam.\n\nNotably, on February 7, Hon’ble Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina virtually inaugurated the competition from Ganobhaban. Over the past years, Quantum Cosmo School and College have consistently achieved excellent results in inter-school winter sports competitions. The boys’ volleyball team has proudly won the national championship six consecutive times, the boys’ table tennis doubles team eight times in a row, and the girls’ table tennis singles and girls’ basketball teams have each won three consecutive national championships, achieving a hat-trick of titles.",
